        {
          "section_title": "Calls for Israel\u2013Hamas war ceasefire",
          "section_content": [
            {
              "sentence": "During the festival, contestants Dargen D'Amico and Ghali made statements calling for a ceasefire in the ongoing Israel\u2013Hamas war, with the latter publicly calling to \"stop the genocide\" after his performance in the final",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "In a tweet, the Israeli ambassador to Italy, Alon Bar, accused Ghali of \"exploiting the festival's stage to spread hate and provocations\", adding that the musical event could have been instead an occasion to express solidarity with the victims of the Re'im music festival massacre",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "In turn, Ghali received praise by the president of the Association of Palestinians in Italy, Mohammad Hannoun, during a demonstration in the artist's home city of Milan",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "The following day, live on the show Domenica in hosted by Mara Venier, Ghali responded to Bar's accusation by recalling his long personal history of speaking out on such topics, pointing out that \"this thing has been going on for a while\" and claiming that \"terror politics\" prevents people from freely calling for peace",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "Shortly after, Venier read out a statement by RAI's CEO Roberto Sergio with an expression of his \"heartfelt and staunch\" solidarity to \"the people of Israel and the Jewish community\"",
              "refs": []
            },
            {
              "sentence": "In response, pro-Palestinian demonstrations broke out between 13 and 17 February outside RAI's production centres of Naples, where a number of protesters were injured in clashes with the police;  Turin\u00a0 [it], where glass bottles, eggs and smoke bombs were thrown;  and Milan\u00a0 [it];  as well as outside the broadcaster's general headquarters in Rome  and its regional offices in Bari\u00a0 [it], Bologna\u00a0 [it], Bolzano\u00a0 [it], Cagliari\u00a0 [it], Cosenza, Florence\u00a0 [it], Genoa\u00a0 [it], Palermo\u00a0 [it], Perugia\u00a0 [it], Pescara\u00a0 [it], Trento\u00a0 [it], Trieste\u00a0 [it] and Venice\u00a0 [it]",
              "refs": [
                "https://www.ansa.it/sanremo_2024/notizie/2024/02/07/body-shaming-verso-bigmama-rai-apre-procedura-disciplinare_0b046d00-600c-46f0-b3c1-274dd5139951.html",
                "https://www.ilmessaggero.it/televisione/john_travolta_inchiesta_scarpe_rai_indagine_cosa_succede_adesso-7925132.html",
                "https://www.escplus.es/sanremo/2024/polemica-en-sanremo-2024-john-travolta-no-da-su-consentimiento-a-la-rai-para-que-vuelvan-a-emitir-las-imagenes-de-su-paso-por-el-festival/",
